request.description:
# Get Post Comments

This endpoint retrieves comments for a specific post identified by the post ID.

## Request

### Request URL

- Method: GET

- URL: {{URL}}/comments/id/post


## Response

The response for this request is a JSON object with the following schema:

``` json
{
  "type": "object",
  "properties": {
    "postId": {
      "type": "number"
    },
    "id": {
      "type": "number"
    },
    "name": {
      "type": "string"
    },
    "email": {
      "type": "string"
    },
    "body": {
      "type": "string"
    }
  }
}

 ```

The response body includes the following fields:

- `postId`: The ID of the post the comment belongs to.

- `id`: The ID of the comment.

- `name`: The name of the commenter.

- `email`: The email of the commenter.

- `body`: The content of the comment.

### Get Comment by ID

This endpoint retrieves a specific comment by its ID.

#### Request

- Method: GET

- URL: `{{URL}}/comments/id`


#### Response

The response for this request follows the JSON schema below:

``` json
{
  "type": "object",
  "properties": {
    "id": {
      "type": "integer"
    },
    "text": {
      "type": "string"
    },
    "author": {
      "type": "string"
    },
    "timestamp": {
      "type": "string",
      "format": "date-time"
    }
  }
}

 ```

### Update Comment

This endpoint is used to update a specific comment by its ID.

#### Request

- Method: PUT

- URL: {{URL}}/comments/id

- Body:

    - `comment`: (text) The updated content of the comment.


#### Response

The response of this request is a JSON object conforming to the following schema:

``` json
{
  "type": "object",
  "properties": {
    "id": {
      "type": "string"
    },
    "content": {
      "type": "string"
    },
    "author": {
      "type": "string"
    },
    "updatedAt": {
      "type": "string",
      "format": "date-time"
    }
  }
}

 ```

response.body:
{
    "error": "Content, post, and author are required for a full update"
}

